// Workflow State Machine
// Defines all workflow states and their conditional transitions.
// Also provides utility functions for querying and mutating work item status.

The workflow has two modes: structured (guided multi-phase flow) and vibe (freeform).
Structured flow: collab-start → gather-goals → brainstorm phase (per-item) →
  rough-draft phase (code/bugfix items) → execution phase (batches) → review → cleanup.
Routing nodes (skill: null) are traversed automatically by the transition engine.
Legacy states are retained for backwards compatibility but new sessions do not enter them.

FUNCTION getDisplayName(state, previousState?) -> string                         EXPORT
  Look up the state in STATE_DISPLAY_NAMES. Return the mapped name if found, else return the state as-is.

---

FUNCTION getWorkflowStates() -> WorkflowState[]                                  EXPORT
  Return the full WORKFLOW_STATES array.

---

FUNCTION getState(id) -> WorkflowState | undefined                               EXPORT
  Find and return the state with the given ID, or undefined.

---

FUNCTION getSkillForState(id) -> string | null                                   EXPORT
  Return the skill name for a state, or null if the state has no skill or doesn't exist.

---

FUNCTION skillToState(skill) -> StateId | null                                   EXPORT
  Find the first state whose skill field matches the given skill name.
  Return its ID, or null if no match.

---

FUNCTION findNextPendingItem(workItems) -> WorkItem | undefined                  EXPORT
  Return the first item whose status is not 'complete', or undefined if all are complete.

---

FUNCTION findNextPendingBrainstormItem(workItems) -> WorkItem | undefined        EXPORT
  Return the first item with status === 'pending' (not yet brainstormed).

---

FUNCTION findNextPendingRoughDraftItem(workItems) -> WorkItem | undefined        EXPORT
  Return the first code or bugfix item with status === 'brainstormed' (ready for blueprint).

---

FUNCTION updateItemStatus(item, newStatus) -> WorkItem                           EXPORT
  Validate that newStatus is a legal transition from item.status using VALID_STATUS_TRANSITIONS.
  Throw if the transition is invalid. Return a new WorkItem with the updated status (immutable).

---

FUNCTION getCurrentWorkItem(workItems, currentItemNumber?) -> WorkItem | undefined  EXPORT
  Return the work item matching currentItemNumber, or undefined if not provided or not found.

---

FUNCTION migrateWorkItems(items) -> WorkItem[]                                   EXPORT
  Map over items and upgrade legacy statuses:
  'documented' → 'brainstormed'
  'interface', 'pseudocode', 'skeleton' → 'complete'
  Return a new array (non-mutating).

---

FUNCTION isImplementationState(state) -> boolean                                 EXPORT
  Return true if the state belongs to the implementation phase
  (execute-batch, batch-router, log-batch-complete, ready-to-implement, bug-review, completeness-review).

---

FUNCTION getNextState(currentState, sessionState) -> string | null               EXPORT
  CALLS: getNextStateForPhaseBatching (transitions)
  Delegate to getNextStateForPhaseBatching from the transitions module.
